subject: p18417750
Findings: There is a dual lead pacemaker/ICD device whose leads terminate in the right atrium and ventricle, respectively, without significant change. The heart is again moderately enlarged. The mediastinal and hilar contours appear stable. The lungs are clear. There are no pleural effusions or pneumothorax. Calcified enthesopathy projects along the greater tuberosity of the left humerus.
